-- U.S. sues Lloyds TSB Bank, Bank of Cyprus
-- 
-- Mon Oct 15, 2007 5:13pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/15/us-lloyds-bankofcyprus-suit-idUSN1537350920071015

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - U.S. prosecutors said on Monday they had filed civil money laundering charges against Lloyds TSB Bank Plc and the Bank of Cyprus, alleging the banks permitted laundering of hundreds of millions of dollars generated in a securities fraud case. 

 The government is seeks monetary civil penalties of at least $130 million from Lloyds TSB Bank Plc and at least $162 million from Bank of Cyprus, the U.S. attorney's office in Manhattan said.